{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01BZaYiJvLTQQoRzJbFzyBFp","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Prototype Creator\n2\t\n3\tPhase 2 (\"the SHOW\") of Red Hat's [AI-SDLC Pipeline](ai-sdlc-pipeline.md). Takes RFE user stories and produces rapid prototypes that make the proposed experience tangible before engineering commits.\n4\t\n5\t## What It Does\n6\t\n7\tGiven an RFE from the [RFE Creator](rfe-creator.md) pipeline or Jira directly, this pipeline:\n8\t\n9\t1. **Create** — Generates a prototype from RFE user stories at a specified fidelity level\n10\t2. **Review** — Scores against a 4-dimension [UX Quality Rubric](ux-quality-rubric.md)\n11\t3. **Refine** — Iterates based on review feedback and human direction\n12\t4. **Test** — Runs simulated usability and desirability testing\n13\t5. **Submit** — Publishes the finished prototype to a target system\n14\t\n15\t## Two Modes\n16\t\n17\t- `--mode=auto` (CI/batch) — AI makes all design decisions autonomously. Good for low-fidelity at scale.\n18\t- `--mode=decide` (human-in-the-loop) — Stops at each design decision point and produces a [Decision Kit](decision-kit.md) artifact with options, previews, tradeoffs. Nothing advances without human judgment.\n19\t\n20\t## Fidelity Levels\n21\t\n22\t- **Low** — Wireframe, placeholder boxes, static (~2–3 min)\n23\t- **Medium** — PatternFly 6 components, key flows (~5–10 min)\n24\t- **High** — Production-ready, all flows + edge cases (~15–30 min)\n25\t\n26\t## Standalone vs. Workspace Mode\n27\t\n28\t- **Standalone** — Self-contained HTML files using PatternFly CDN\n29\t- **Workspace** (`--workspace`) — Targets an existing codebase, analyzes tech stack, generates code that fits the project (React, Angular, etc.)\n30\t\n31\t## Key Constraints\n32\t\n33\t- Internal GitLab instance does not support unique URLs per merge request via GitLab Pages\n34\t- Prototypes must be served via localhost during evaluation\n35\t- Code Rabbit not available on internal GitLab — custom commenting needed\n36\t\n37\t## Evaluator Super Agent (Evan's assignment)\n38\t\n39\tBuilding an evaluator that combines usability testing, desirability testing, consistency checking (Bo Morley's tool), and design feasibility scoring. Uses Jira as context source. Posts automated feedback on merge requests.\n40\t\n41\tSee: [Evaluator Super Agent](evaluator-super-agent.md)\n42\t\n43\t## Related\n44\t\n45\t- [Outcome Tiger Team](outcome-tiger-team.md) — Workstream 2 proposes E2E prototype validation against outcome goals\n46\t- [Prototype Creator Demo — May 14](prototype-creator-demo-may14.md) — full walkthrough of both workflows with team discussion\n47\t- [AI-SDLC Pipeline](ai-sdlc-pipeline.md) — the three-phase pipeline\n48\t- [Decision Kit](decision-kit.md) — integrated for human-in-the-loop decisions\n49\t- [Agent Eval Harness](agent-eval-harness.md) — for evaluating skill quality\n50\t- [UX Quality Rubric](ux-quality-rubric.md) — scoring system\n51\t- [Session Log — 2026-06-15](session-log-2026-06-15.md) — crafted Slack response about prototype-evaluate for #wg-agent-eval-harness\n52\t- [Ansible AI Helpers Strategy — 2026-06-17](ansible-ai-helpers-strategy-2026-06-17.md) — next candidate for Ansible integration after heuristic eval pilot\n53\t- [RH AI-First UX — 2026-06-18](rh-ai-first-ux-2026-06-18.md) — GitLab pages routing fix enables multi-prototype hosting; Evan demoed evaluate work\n54\t- [Andy/Evan Meeting — June 22](andy-evan-2026-06-22.md) — cost strategy for Prototype Creator invocation in eval loop\n55\t- [Zack/Evan Meeting — June 24](zack-evan-2026-06-24.md) — Jira epic structure, skill architecture, context window limits\n56\t- [AI-First Sync — June 25](ai-first-sync-2026-06-25.md) — 3.6 branch strategy, centralized reporting goals\n57\t- [Andy/Evan Meeting — June 29](andy-evan-2026-06-29.md) — sub-skill structure, RF→Strat entity linking, token optimization\n58\t- [Midpoint Check-in — June 30](midpoint-checkin-2026-06-30.md) — where prototype creator fits in ADLC still TBD, report as product\n59\t\n60\t## Sources\n61\t\n62\t- sources/2026-06-09-prototype-creator-overview.html\n63\t- [andybraren/prototype-creator](https://github.com/andybraren/prototype-creator) (GitHub)\n64\t- Andy/Evan meeting notes — 2026-06-08\n65\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e62685c4-83ff-4153-a044-58d10058f32c","uuid":"fe3dc654-e9ef-447d-82d6-10983bf59cca","timestamp":"2026-07-09T16:04:59.129Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ejaquez/second-brain/wiki/prototype-creator.md","content":"# Prototype Creator\n\nPhase 2 (\"the SHOW\") of Red Hat's [AI-SDLC Pipeline](ai-sdlc-pipeline.md). Takes RFE user stories and produces rapid prototypes that make the proposed experience tangible before engineering commits.\n\n## What It Does\n\nGiven an RFE from the [RFE Creator](rfe-creator.md) pipeline or Jira directly, this pipeline:\n\n1. **Create** — Generates a prototype from RFE user stories at a specified fidelity level\n2. **Review** — Scores against a 4-dimension [UX Quality Rubric](ux-quality-rubric.md)\n3. **Refine** — Iterates based on review feedback and human direction\n4. **Test** — Runs simulated usability and desirability testing\n5. **Submit** — Publishes the finished prototype to a target system\n\n## Two Modes\n\n- `--mode=auto` (CI/batch) — AI makes all design decisions autonomously. Good for low-fidelity at scale.\n- `--mode=decide` (human-in-the-loop) — Stops at each design decision point and produces a [Decision Kit](decision-kit.md) artifact with options, previews, tradeoffs. Nothing advances without human judgment.\n\n## Fidelity Levels\n\n- **Low** — Wireframe, placeholder boxes, static (~2–3 min)\n- **Medium** — PatternFly 6 components, key flows (~5–10 min)\n- **High** — Production-ready, all flows + edge cases (~15–30 min)\n\n## Standalone vs. Workspace Mode\n\n- **Standalone** — Self-contained HTML files using PatternFly CDN\n- **Workspace** (`--workspace`) — Targets an existing codebase, analyzes tech stack, generates code that fits the project (React, Angular, etc.)\n\n## Key Constraints\n\n- Internal GitLab instance does not support unique URLs per merge request via GitLab Pages\n- Prototypes must be served via localhost during evaluation\n- Code Rabbit not available on internal GitLab — custom commenting needed\n\n## Evaluator Super Agent (Evan's assignment)\n\nBuilding an evaluator that combines usability testing, desirability testing, consistency checking (Bo Morley's tool), and design feasibility scoring. Uses Jira as context source. Posts automated feedback on merge requests.\n\nSee: [Evaluator Super Agent](evaluator-super-agent.md)\n\n## Related\n\n- [Outcome Tiger Team](outcome-tiger-team.md) — Workstream 2 proposes E2E prototype validation against outcome goals\n- [Prototype Creator Demo — May 14](prototype-creator-demo-may14.md) — full walkthrough of both workflows with team discussion\n- [AI-SDLC Pipeline](ai-sdlc-pipeline.md) — the three-phase pipeline\n- [Decision Kit](decision-kit.md) — integrated for human-in-the-loop decisions\n- [Agent Eval Harness](agent-eval-harness.md) — for evaluating skill quality\n- [UX Quality Rubric](ux-quality-rubric.md) — scoring system\n- [Session Log — 2026-06-15](session-log-2026-06-15.md) — crafted Slack response about prototype-evaluate for #wg-agent-eval-harness\n- [Ansible AI Helpers Strategy — 2026-06-17](ansible-ai-helpers-strategy-2026-06-17.md) — next candidate for Ansible integration after heuristic eval pilot\n- [RH AI-First UX — 2026-06-18](rh-ai-first-ux-2026-06-18.md) — GitLab pages routing fix enables multi-prototype hosting; Evan demoed evaluate work\n- [Andy/Evan Meeting — June 22](andy-evan-2026-06-22.md) — cost strategy for Prototype Creator invocation in eval loop\n- [Zack/Evan Meeting — June 24](zack-evan-2026-06-24.md) — Jira epic structure, skill architecture, context window limits\n- [AI-First Sync — June 25](ai-first-sync-2026-06-25.md) — 3.6 branch strategy, centralized reporting goals\n- [Andy/Evan Meeting — June 29](andy-evan-2026-06-29.md) — sub-skill structure, RF→Strat entity linking, token optimization\n- [Midpoint Check-in — June 30](midpoint-checkin-2026-06-30.md) — where prototype creator fits in ADLC still TBD, report as product\n\n## Sources\n\n- sources/2026-06-09-prototype-creator-overview.html\n- [andybraren/prototype-creator](https://github.com/andybraren/prototype-creator) (GitHub)\n- Andy/Evan meeting notes — 2026-06-08\n","numLines":65,"startLine":1,"totalLines":65}}}
