ly 6 migration, and rubric methodology.\n\n## Key Points\n\n- Reviewed prototype evaluation results from the last sprint\n- Andy: PatternFly 6 migration targeting Q3\n- Zack raised usability testing automation progress as a question\n- Action item: Evan to demo [Evaluator Super Agent](evaluator-super-agent.md) next week (week of July 7)\n- Agreed to use [Nielsen's 10 Heuristics](nielsens-heuristics-jagged-edge.md) as the base rubric for evaluations\n- Next meeting agenda: revisit scoring dimensions (see [UX Quality Rubric](ux-quality-rubric.md))\n\n## Related\n\n- [Evaluator Super Agent](evaluator-super-agent.md) — Evan demoing this next week; central topic of discussion\n- [Nielsen's Heuristics & The Jagged Edge](nielsens-heuristics-jagged-edge.md) — agreed as base rubric methodology\n- [UX Quality Rubric](ux-quality-rubric.md) — scoring dimensions flagged for next meeting revisit\n- [Prototype Creator](prototype-creator.md) — evaluation results from last sprint discussed\n- [Midpoint Check-in — June 30](midpoint-checkin-2026-06-30.md) — Zack's prior feedback and context for this meeting\n\n## Sources\n\n- ~/second-brain/sources/weekly-design-sync-2026-07-01.md\n- Ingested: 2026-07-09\n","numLines":26,"startLine":1,"totalLines":26}}}
{"type": "assistant", "message": {"model": "claude-opus-4-6", "id": "msg_vrtx_01LGqcu2hDLqzqMYdib7Lveh", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Here's what your wiki knows about **usability testing**:\n\n---\n\n## Direct Matches\n\n### [Evaluator Super Agent](~/second-brain/wiki/evaluator-super-agent.md) \u2014 your primary work\nYour main assignment: an automated prototype quality assessment agent that runs simulated usability testing via Playwright persona walkthroughs. **Status: Shipped** on branch `evan/prototype-evaluate` at `andybraren/prototype-creator`. Key capabilities:\n- **7-dimension usability scoring** with persona overlays (Zack Bodnar's framework)\n- **Playwright-based persona journeys** evaluated against Jira acceptance criteria\n- **3-phase pipeline**: extract ACs/personas \u2192 Playwright walkthroughs + consistency check \u2192 usability dimension scoring \u2192 HTML report + Google Sheet sync\n- Research references include **Avenir-UX** (autonomous UX eval agent using SEQ/SUS) and **UXCascade** (multi-agent persona simulation with severity-rated issues S1\u2013S4)\n- A feedback loop (eval \u2192 prototype-refine \u2192 re-eval, max 3 iterations) is in progress\n\n### [Nielsen's 10 Usability Heuristics](~/second-brain/wiki/nielsens-10-usability-heuristics.md)\nFoundational reference \u2014 Jakob Nielsen's 1994 heuristics (visibility, match to real world, user control, consistency, error prevention, recognition over recall, flexibility, minimalist design, error recovery, help/docs). Your team adopted these as the **base rubric** for all evaluations (confirmed at the July 1 design sync).\n\n### [Nielsen's Heuristics & The Jagged Edge](~/second-brain/wiki/nielsens-heuristics-jagged-edge.md)\nYour first internship assignment: applied heuristic evaluation across Cursor, Claude Code, Gemini, and ChatGPT to Kubernetes/OpenShift UI screens. Compared analysis quality, depth, specificity, hallucinations, and unique insights. This directly informed the Evaluator Super Agent's methodology.\n\n### [UX Quality Rubric](~/second-brain/wiki/ux-quality-rubric.md)\nThe 4-dimension scoring system (Completeness, Usability, Feasibility, Fidelity Match) used by Prototype Creator. The **Usability** dimension is grounded in Nielsen's heuristics. Pass threshold: 6+ total with no zeros.\n\n---\n\n## Related Context\n\n- **Testing fragmentation concern** ([RH AI-First UX \u2014 June 25](~/second-brain/wiki/rh-ai-first-ux-2026-06-25.md)): Zack flagged proliferation of varied usability testing tools across the org. Yahav was assigned to draft a unified testing strategy proposal.\n- **\"Automated usability testing\"** is one of your listed active projects in the config \u2014 a simulated testing tool with persona YAML files and an evaluate-flow protocol.\n- The [Prototype Creator](~/second-brain/wiki/prototype-creator.md) pipeline includes a dedicated \"Test\" phase that runs simulated usability and desirability testing.\n- At the [Weekly Design Sync \u2014 July 1](~/second-brain/wiki/weekly-design-sync-2026-07-01.md), the team agreed on Nielsen's heuristics as the base rubric, and you're demoing the evaluator the week of July 7.\n- At the [Midpoint Check-in \u2014 June 30](~/second-brain/wiki/midpoint-checkin-2026-06-30.md), Zack called this \"pioneering work\" combining research + AI + SDLC.\n\n---\n\n## Knowledge Gaps\n\n- No dedicated wiki page yet for the **automated-usability-testing** project itself (it's an active project in config but documented only through the Evaluator Super Agent page)\n- No page covering **Yahav's unified testing strategy proposal** (assigned June 25 \u2014 may have been drafted since)\n- No wiki page on **Avenir-UX** or **UXCascade** as standalone references (only mentioned within the Evaluator page)\n- No page on **desirability testing** as a distinct concept (mentioned alongside usability testing in Prototype Creator but not elaborated)"}], "stop_reason": null, "stop_sequence": null, "stop_details": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 1, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 2820, "cache_read_input_tokens": 42345, "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 2820, "ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0}, "output_tokens": 1}, "context_management": null}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "e62685c4-83ff-4153-a044-58d10058f32c", "uuid": "550bea3c-7235-432d-8b5c-74035aac288d", "request_id": "req_vrtx_011CcrmXHu76VPbzH2swDTcs", "timestamp": "2026-07-09T16:05:24.689Z"}
